<item>
            <title>[LU-6960] Can not overwrite existing mgsnode param via tunefs.lustre</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6960</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we want to change MGS node, we need change mgsnode param for all OST devices, and &quot;tunefs.lustre --mgsnode &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;device&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot; will only append this MGS node nid to existing ones. I think it should replace the old ones, the multiple --mgsnode would be using append mode only, like &quot;tunefs.lustre --mgsnode nid1 --mgsnode nid2 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;device&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot; will replace all old mgsnode param on the device, and save these two new MGS nids to it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
